## Step 2: Calculate the probability of drawing two balls of the same color
The probability of drawing two red balls is $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{x}{x+9}$, and the probability of drawing two blue balls is $\frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{x+9}$. Therefore, the total probability of drawing two balls of the same color is $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{x}{x+9} + \frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{x+9}$.

