## Step 2
We know that $P(P \cup C) + P(P' \cap C') = 1$. So, $P(P \cup C) = 1 - P(P' \cap C') = 1 - 0.08 = 0.92$.

## Step 3
Using the inclusion-exclusion principle, $P(P \cup C) = P(P) + P(C) - P(P \cap C)$. Substituting the given values, we have $0.92 = P(P) + P(C) - 0.28$.

## Step 4
Rearranging the equation from Step 3 gives $P(P) + P(C) = 0.92 + 0.28 = 1.20$.

## Step 5
From Step 1, we have $P(P) = P(C) + 0.16$. We can substitute $P(P)$ in the equation from Step 4 to get $P(C) + 0.16 + P(C) = 1.20$. This simplifies to $2P(C) + 0.16 = 1.20$.

## Step 6
