Given that 17% of patients have an irregular heartbeat and 35% of those with an irregular heartbeat have high blood pressure, we can find the percentage of patients with both irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure. This is calculated as 35% of 17% = 0.35 * 17% = 5.95%.

