## Step 5: Convert $E_{v=0}$ from $\mathrm{cm}^{-1}$ to $\mathrm{eV}$.
To convert $\mathrm{cm}^{-1}$ to $\mathrm{eV}$, we use the conversion factor $1 \, \mathrm{eV} = 8065.54 \, \mathrm{cm}^{-1}$. Thus, $E_{v=0} \, \text{in eV} = \frac{697.025}{8065.54}$.

## Step 6: Perform the conversion calculation.
